It might seem like some kind of belated April Fool's campaign for Coke, but Kendall Jenner's Pepsi commercial has done the impossible and united the internet -- just not in the way it wanted. The ad, which is being universally panned for it's tone-deaf approach and commercialisation of social issues, features Jenner joining a protest and handing a policeman a cool, refreshing Pepsi, subsequently ending society's woes. Naturally Twitter had a few thoughts on that. Here are just a few of the reactions to the ad.                                  theory: that Kendall Jenner Pepsi ad is actually a Coke ad    Pepsi is NOT okay.   ALSO ON HUFFPOST AUSTRALIA  HuffPost AustraliaFollow On 